== Race report ==
Kimi Antonelli (Mercedes) started from pole position ahead of Charles Leclerc (Ferrari).

Antonelli quickly reduced Leclerc's advantage after the restart and had brought the gap down to just over three seconds when he reported a problem with his car on lap 41.

Mercedes initially changed the front wing and tyres, but identified the problem as a broken left-front wheel shield.

Antonelli made a second stop to remove the damaged bodywork and returned to the circuit in tenth place, struggling with the handling of the car.

He received a five-second penalty for exceeding track limits, which later dropped him from ninth on the road to sixteenth in the final classification.

On lap 39, Nico Hülkenberg (Audi) stopped at the side of the circuit with a hydraulic problem, causing a second virtual safety car period.

Hamilton was noted for a potential false start and subsequently received a five-second time penalty.
